  "text": "In contrast, Sa12 derivatives mimicking eukaryotic 28S rRNA or specific 23S rRNA mutations that render bacteria resistant to MLS antibiotics (S. aureus 23S rRNA A2085G, mimicked by ORN Sa12s6G or Sa12s6U) failed to stimulate bone marrow cells (Fig. 3F and table S1 ) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . These findings suggest that molecular mechanisms rendering bacteria resistant to naturally occurring antibiotics also impede MyD88 dependent host recognition by an ill-defined endosomal TLR.",
